Commentary Text: Dwayne Bravo to Dhawan, out Caught by Jadeja!! There is the experience of Dwayne Bravo for you. He bowls these floaty full balls to invite the batter for a big hit, but he knows he's set a trap and batters keep falling prey. Wide slower delivery outside off stump, Dhawan toe-ends the lofted drive, Jadeja runs to his right and takes an easy catch. In the context of the game this is a massive wicket because Dhawan can anchor the innings all the way for others to throw their willows around him. Dhawan c Jadeja b Dwayne Bravo 33(24) [4s-4 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Jordan to Rajapaksa, out Rajapaksa Run Out!! Huge mix-up. The fielder misses the direct-hit, Dhoni runs in as cover and underarms as he is not close to the stumps. Hits direct and look at that smile. That confident smile is enough to say Rajapaksa is short here even before the third ump checks. And the replay confirms Rajapaksa is well short. What a disastrous start for PBKS. He pushed this to the left of the bowler and took off. Wonder if he didn't hear Dhawan's call or if Dhawan sold him down the river. Rajapaksa was midway and had too much ground to cover. Jordan and Dhoni did the rest. Looks like Dhawan just took a step towards the striker's end and that probably tricked Rajapaksa into thinking the run was on. Dhoni was so alert to the situation that he had to cover the throw. Smart! Rajapaksa run out (Jordan/Dhoni) 9(5) [6s-1]

Commentary Text: Odean Smith to Rayudu, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! Five down! Rayudu's gone as well. Wow what a performance this has been from the Punjab pacers so far as Smith joins the party as well. Short of length delivery that shapes back into Rayudu this time, unlike the previous one that went away. He tries to ramp it again but gets cramped for room with the ball coming back. It goes off his gloves to the right of the keeper who takes a brilliant diving catch. Rayudu c Jitesh Sharma b Odean Smith 13(21) [4s-2]
